VPN is bullshit. they provide neither anonymity nor security. VPN was made to securely access a remote network. Your IP isn't as important as they make it out to be. if you want anonymity use tor. if you want to mask your ip, use a proxy (or tor). your browser sends a load of information that can be used to identify you uniquely, from the version and operating system in the user agent to screen resolution, supported ciphers and loads of other stuff. cookies can be used to track you easily. as soon as you log in they know who you are anyway. as for security... it does nothing. packets are encrypted with vpn to the vpn server and then the vpn layer is decrypted. that's not a problem since 99.5% of the internet uses TLS with AES anyway. It doesn't protect you from scams, downloading viruses or entering your credit card information on fake banking sites. Also instead of your ISP getting all of your DNS requests, the vpn server gets them (as well as all 100% of your decrypted (vpn layer only, obviously) traffic), so who do you trust more? I'd rather trust myself. If you do want your dns records secure just set up a recursive dns server. i have one running on my raspberry pi as well as my own openvpn server. and not because of the bullshit reasons vpn companies sell you but because to access my own network (printer, network storage, etc) from remote. So instead of selling that vpn snakeoil, how about you choose your sponsors more carefully. at least raid shadow legends is providing a game, however shitty, instead of taking your money for nothing except for a slower internet connection and potential security risk. And yes, using VPN is a security risk. You're literally plugging a (virtual) lan cable into their vpn server, bypassing any and all protection layers like your router's NAS firewall and IDS and instead rely on theirs. I can connect to my home VPN server all I want because I know it's secure and it has snort ids set up (on the raspberry), pi hole (on the pi), my nextcloud storage and webserver (on the pi), the recursive dns server (on the pi), etc. So literally buy a raspberry pi for 40 bucks and you get more value out of it than all the fucking vpn salesmen in the world. and even if you don't you don't get anything. vpn providers have a place, but it's not like everybody needs it or their data gets stolen by hackers. that's not how hacking works, or vpn. you go to a malicious website that exploits some vulnerability in your browser or execute a virus or run an vulnerable service like a game server or something and the hacker just gets the data through the vpn tunnel just like anything else. The best defense is not vpn, it's brain.exe running properly. and that includes not buying this bullshit. so stop promoting it. please. PS: also just because raid shadow legends is better than vpn... please do not promote that garbage either. and although i'm sick of hearing it, audibile and brilliant at least offer something sensible.
